{"parse":{"title":"College of Islamic and Arabic Studies, Afghanistan","pageid":22519108,"revid":802322847,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\">For other uses, see <a href=\"/wiki/College_of_Islamic_and_Arabic_Studies_(disambiguation)\" class=\"mw-redirect mw-disambig\" title=\"College of Islamic and Arabic Studies (disambiguation)\">College of Islamic and Arabic Studies</a>.</div>\n<p>The <b>College of Islamic and Arabic Studies</b> in <a href=\"/wiki/Afghanistan\" title=\"Afghanistan\">Afghanistan</a> was an organization where American <a href=\"/wiki/Intelligence_analysts\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Intelligence analysts\">intelligence analysts</a> asserted was tied to <a href=\"/wiki/Al_Qaeda\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Al Qaeda\">al Qaeda</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-longwar2011-04-10_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-longwar2011-04-10-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\nThey reported that <a href=\"/wiki/Mahfouz_Ould_al-Walid\" title=\"Mahfouz Ould al-Walid\">Mahfouz Ould al-Walid</a>, better known as <i>\"Abu Hafs al-Mauritani\"</i>, the director of the institution, was a senior member of al Qaeda's leadership circle.\nWhen analysts went over the grounds of the institute they found what they characterized as <i>\"<a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Martyrship_videos&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Martyrship videos (page does not exist)\">martyrship videos</a>\"</i>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Arb2SummaryOfEvidenceAbdALRahimAbdulRazaJanko_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Arb2SummaryOfEvidenceAbdALRahimAbdulRazaJanko-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Guantanamo_captive\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Guantanamo captive\">Guantanamo captive</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Abd_Al_Rahim_Abdul_Rassak_Janko\" title=\"Abd Al Rahim Abdul Rassak Janko\">Abd Al Rahim Abdul Rassak Janko</a> testified that the recording of him was not a martyrship video at all, but rather a confession.  He acknowledged that he had travelled to Afghanistan, in 2000, to offer his services to the <a href=\"/wiki/Taliban\" title=\"Taliban\">Taliban</a>, but he had inadvertently triggered the suspicion he was an <a href=\"/wiki/Israel\" title=\"Israel\">Israeli</a> or <a href=\"/wiki/United_States\" title=\"United States\">American</a> spy.  He asserted that the Taliban turned him over to the Taliban to torture a confession out of him, and that the recording was the confession that followed his torture.  He asserted he was interrogated and tortured at the institute for two weeks.\n</p><p>According to <a href=\"/wiki/Gabriel_Weimann\" title=\"Gabriel Weimann\">Gabriel Weimann</a>, in <i>\"Responses to cyber terrorism\"</i>, the institute ran a virtual magazine dedicated to promoting global jihad, entitled <i>\"<a href=\"/wiki/Sawt_al-Jihad\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sawt al-Jihad\">Sawt al-Jihad</a>\"</i>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-IosPress2008_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-IosPress2008-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=College_of_Islamic_and_Arabic_Studies,_Afghanistan&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-longwar2011-04-10-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-longwar2011-04-10_1-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">\n<cite class=\"citation news\"><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Thomas_Joscelyn&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Thomas Joscelyn (page does not exist)\">Thomas Joscelyn</a> (2011-04-10). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.longwarjournal.org/archives/2011/04/al_qaeda_fighter_pro.php\">\"Al Qaeda fighter properly detained at Gitmo, court finds\"</a>. <i><a href=\"/wiki/Long_War_Journal\" title=\"Long War Journal\">Long War Journal</a></i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">October 23,</span> 2012</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Long+War+Journal&amp;rft.atitle=Al+Qaeda+fighter+properly+detained+at+Gitmo%2C+court+finds&amp;rft.date=2011-04-10&amp;rft.au=Thomas+Joscelyn&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.longwarjournal.org%2Farchives%2F2011%2F04%2Fal_qaeda_fighter_pro.php&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACollege+of+Islamic+and+Arabic+Studies%2C+Afghanistan\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Arb2SummaryOfEvidenceAbdALRahimAbdulRazaJanko-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-Arb2SummaryOfEvidenceAbdALRahimAbdulRazaJanko_2-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">\n<cite class=\"citation web\"><a href=\"/wiki/OARDEC\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"OARDEC\">OARDEC</a> (26 June 2006). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.dod.mil/pubs/foi/detainees/csrt_arb/ARB_Round_2_Factors_499-598.pdf#73\">\"Unclassified Summary of Evidence for Administrative Review Board in the case of Janko, Abd AL Rahim Abdul Raza\"</a> <span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(PDF)</span>. <a href=\"/wiki/United_States_Department_of_Defense\" title=\"United States Department of Defense\">United States Department of Defense</a>. pp.&#160;<b>pages 73\u201375</b><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2008-05-05</span></span>. <q>The detainee stated that he was held for approximately two weeks at a <a href=\"/wiki/Taliban_guest_house\" title=\"Taliban guest house\">guest house</a> known as <b>College of Islamic and Arabic Studies</b> where he was interrogated and tortured.</q></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Unclassified+Summary+of+Evidence+for+Administrative+Review+Board+in+the+case+of+Janko%2C+Abd+AL+Rahim+Abdul+Raza&amp;rft.pages=%27%27%27pages+73-75%27%27%27&amp;rft.pub=United+States+Department+of+Defense&amp;rft.date=2006-06-26&amp;rft.au=OARDEC&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.dod.mil%2Fpubs%2Ffoi%2Fdetainees%2Fcsrt_arb%2FARB_Round_2_Factors_499-598.pdf%2373&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACollege+of+Islamic+and+Arabic+Studies%2C+Afghanistan\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-IosPress2008-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-IosPress2008_3-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">\n<cite class=\"citation news\">Gabriel Weimann (2008). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=tFmxVnDhBRQC&amp;pg=PA67&amp;dq=martyr+%22Arabic+Studies%22+OR+%22Islamic+Studies%22+kandahar+OR+%22al+qaeda%22+OR+%22osama+bin+laden%22+OR+%22abu+hafs%22&amp;hl=en&amp;sa=X&amp;ei=lb-qUdfgIYmpqgHcuIGQCA&amp;redir_esc=y#v=onepage&amp;q=martyr%20%22Arabic%20Studies%22%20OR%20%22Islamic%20Studies%22%20kandahar%20OR%20%22al%20qaeda%22%20OR%20%22osama%20bin%20laden%22%20OR%20%22abu%20hafs%22&amp;f=false\">\"Responses to cyber terrorism\"</a>. <a href=\"/wiki/IOS_Press\" title=\"IOS Press\">IOS Press</a>. p.&#160;67. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/9781586038366\" title=\"Special:BookSources/9781586038366\">9781586038366</a><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2013-06-02</span></span>. <q>Another online channel used to promote the ideological legitimacy of global jihad is the Web site of al Qaeda's Center for Islamic Studies and Research.  This Web site has published the bimonthly virtual magazine <i>Sawt al-Jihad</i>, or <i>The Voice of Jihad.</i></q></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Responses+to+cyber+terrorism&amp;rft.pages=67&amp;rft.date=2008&amp;rft.isbn=9781586038366&amp;rft.au=Gabriel+Weimann&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DtFmxVnDhBRQC%26pg%3DPA67%26dq%3Dmartyr%2B%2522Arabic%2BStudies%2522%2BOR%2B%2522Islamic%2BStudies%2522%2Bkandahar%2BOR%2B%2522al%2Bqaeda%2522%2BOR%2B%2522osama%2Bbin%2Bladen%2522%2BOR%2B%2522abu%2Bhafs%2522%26hl%3Den%26sa%3DX%26ei%3Dlb-qUdfgIYmpqgHcuIGQCA%26redir_esc%3Dy%23v%3Donepage%26q%3Dmartyr%2520%2522Arabic%2520Studies%2522%2520OR%2520%2522Islamic%2520Studies%2522%2520kandahar%2520OR%2520%2522al%2520qaeda%2522%2520OR%2520%2522osama%2520bin%2520laden%2522%2520OR%2520%2522abu%2520hafs%2522%26f%3Dfalse&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACollege+of+Islamic+and+Arabic+Studies%2C+Afghanistan\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n<p><span id=\"coordinates\" class=\"metadata coord-missing\"></span>\n</p><p><br />\n</p>\n<table class=\"metadata plainlinks stub\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"background:transparent\"><tbody><tr><td><a href=\"/wiki/File:Flag_map_of_Afghanistan.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Stub icon\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d1/Flag_map_of_Afghanistan.svg/50px-Flag_map_of_Afghanistan.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"38\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d1/Flag_map_of_Afghanistan.svg/75px-Flag_map_of_Afghanistan.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d1/Flag_map_of_Afghanistan.svg/100px-Flag_map_of_Afghanistan.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"789\" data-file-height=\"607\" /></a></td><td><i>This <a href=\"/wiki/Afghanistan\" title=\"Afghanistan\">Afghanistan</a>-related article is a <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Stub\" title=\"Wikipedia:Stub\">stub</a>. You can help Wikipedia b